From: Liu Jian <liujian56@huawei.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2020 22:31:49 +0800
Subject: mlxsw: destroy workqueue when trap_register in mlxsw_emad_init
Git-commit: 5dbaeb87f2b309936be0aeae00cbc9e7f20ab296
Patch-mainline: 5.8-rc7
References: networking-stable-20_07_29

When mlxsw_core_trap_register fails in mlxsw_emad_init,
destroy_workqueue() shouled be called to destroy mlxsw_core->emad_wq.

Fixes: d965465b60ba ("mlxsw: core: Fix possible deadlock")
Signed-off-by: Liu Jian <liujian56@huawei.com>
Reviewed-by: Ido Schimmel <idosch@mellanox.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlxsw/core.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlxsw/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlxsw/core.c
@@ -709,7 +709,7 @@ static int mlxsw_emad_init(struct mlxsw_
 	err = mlxsw_core_trap_register(mlxsw_core, &mlxsw_emad_rx_listener,
 				       mlxsw_core);
 	if (err)
-		return err;
+		goto err_trap_register;
 
 	err = mlxsw_core->driver->basic_trap_groups_set(mlxsw_core);
 	if (err)
@@ -721,6 +721,7 @@ static int mlxsw_emad_init(struct mlxsw_
 err_emad_trap_set:
 	mlxsw_core_trap_unregister(mlxsw_core, &mlxsw_emad_rx_listener,
 				   mlxsw_core);
+err_trap_register:
 	destroy_workqueue(mlxsw_core->emad_wq);
 	return err;
 }
